Ok, I will try to break this down as well as I can. The service and atmosphere were fantastic. The food was good. Now, let me explain why the food was only good.

The flavors were excellent. The food tasted amazing. But it still left me feeling like it could have been better. You see, like all Chinese restaurants, the menu is enormous. I was there on a Saturday night at 5:30 pm. The middle of the dinner rush. There were only two or three other tables seated the whole time we were there. The only way a restaurant with that size menu, with that many options and with that few customers, could possibly survive is to cook everything from frozen. Like I said, the flavors were on point. The chef who cooked the food knows what he or she is doing and is a talented chef. They are just working with food that stays in the freezer for to long because there aren't enough customers to support a menu that size. The food tasted great, but it also tasted frozen and reheated.

Overall, I will be going back, and I encourage everyone else to go there too. Sunrise needs more business so they can keep their stock rotated and put out the excellent quality food I know they are capable of doing. I would love to see this place packed with a waiting list every weekend night. The kitchen deserves to be recognized for putting out food that tastes that good even with the problems. I would love to see what they can do with fresh ingredients that haven't been frozen.

Yesterday just after noon, six adults, a small child, and I sat down at a table in Sunrise, a Chinese restaurant on South First Street in Abilene, TX.   About four other tables soon were also occupied, with one or two diners at each.  We were aware that the drive-up window service was active. Only one waiter was in the restaurant, which is the consistent staffing pattern at Sunrise.  We do not know what role, if any, the waiter had regarding the drive-up customers.   He came to our table and took an order for a spring roll and an appetizer dish of fried chicken wings, and then left us sitting.  He did not ask what we wanted to drink, and we were served no water or other drinks.  He never came back to finish taking our orders.  One of our party went to the owner and told him we had not been served water nor had our orders been taken, and soon the waiter brought us water.  Eventually he delivered the spring roll and appetizers to our table, but we had no plates to put the appetizers on for each diner, so we used paper napkins to place appetizers in front of each diner.  He still did not ask for our orders.  After waiting a bit longer, one of our party went to the owner and placed our orders with the owner.  Soon the waiter came to our table and yelled loudly at us in Chinese, with a distraught expression on his face, ‚ÄúI am so busy.‚Äù   We had been waiting about 35 min.  By that time we had had enough of the appalling lack of service.  We offered to pay the owner for the appetizers that had been brought to our table.  He said, ‚ÄúForget about it.‚Äù  We left the restaurant still hungry.

reviews.text:
I recently dined at China Star on September 22nd, and I must say I was quite disappointed with both the food and housekeeping conditions. While the staff was exceptionally nice, the overall care of the facility left much to be desired. The condition of the buffet area needed to be cleaned as the backsplash was stained and the glass covering at the buffet was nasty. The bathrooms had the stickiest floor which is due to not changing out the mop water or using a cleaning solution.

Let's start with the food. I had high expectations based on the memories I had as a child, but the quality of the food was poor. The flavors were bland, and the presentation lacked creativity. It felt like the kitchen was cutting corners in terms of quality. For the price I paid, I expected a more memorable dining experience. The best item we had was the Jell-O and that's saying something.

Moving on to the housekeeping, I couldn't help but notice the poor condition of the facility. The tables and floors were visibly dirty, and it was clear that maintenance was lacking. This detracted from the overall ambiance and made it difficult to fully enjoy the meal. Cleanliness should be a basic expectation, especially in a place of this caliber.

I do want to reiterate that the staff was courteous and attentive, which was a redeeming factor in an otherwise disappointing visit. However, I hope the management takes steps to address these issues to provide a better experience for future guests.

I am sadden to see the downward spiral of this establishment as it once was the best Chinese buffet in Abilene at one time.

I loved take out because I get off work late and rather than cooking I want my favorite food.
Which is mostly is Chinese food.
I hardly make it habit to eat take out at China Star.
In these last 2 years 2022 -2023
The food has been either over cooked or raw.

All the meat is too hard to chew, Except for the shrimp.
Even the egg rolls and spring rolls were burnt.

As for the customer service I feel uncomfortable, They were watching me making my go to plate and even left the front desk to do so.
Once I pay they didn‚Äôt mention why they were watching me.
One of the staff even walked me out.
Didn‚Äôt mention a word like have a good day.
This will be my last time going to china star.
If I could I rate 0 stars
Why waste my hard working money on raw food and over cooked food.
I gave this restaurant many chances.
Since I ate at this restaurant with my family when I was younger.

From the plates sticking to the table to our shoes on the floor and it's carpet. It's the most bland food ever! And $7.50 for sweet tea and never got a refill. There's so much steam coming from the food bar with nowhere to go it's a sauna so disappointed.

reviews.text: I've loved this place for decades. It needs to be updated, but that doesn't stand in the way of great food. Their chicken with black bean sauce is amazing. & when I saw it wasn't on the buffett any longer, the owner had some (a full order) made just for me.

reviews.name: amanda odell
reviews.text: The food was excellent, but went to pay signed the ticket added a tip went to wall out the door and the young girl starts saying it declined the card. Gave her another card she says it declined that then gave her a third card she said it declined that  so I told her it has to be her machine  so she puts the card in manually and her machine froze. reviews.name: Steve Alexander
reviews.text:
We're not aware of closure due to roaches and or rats. Only two cars in parking lot. Thought it was still closed, so look up recent news and yes, they were closed. How many times this time.
Surely there has to be a limit on how many times you are closed before being closed for good ? Anyhow, we looked it over. Not good. Hours of operation 4pm till 9 or whatever, which explains that
Food was dried up. Some not even heated ( probably to cut cost ) and all in all. Nothing looked any good or safe to eat considering it was made prior to 4 pm but most likely left over from previous day or worse. So sad. Used to be a good place to eat Chinese food but that time has come and gone. So long from now on from this family that remembers when it opened and See's what it has become.

reviews.name: John Rains
reviews.text:
I grew up in Abilene and China Star was always one of the best buffets. Haven't been back home in a few years so was super excited to go hit the buffet but wow, what a disappointment!?

Every dish on the buffet was soggy, rice noodles were hard and crunchy.. Pepper steak texture seemed it had been out for hours and even the egg roles were burnt on the outside! Just a wad of mush on the inside. Fried fish, rubber.. The only thing that was even remotely enjoyable was the Dr. Pepper!?

A lot of memories eating at this place but I will never go back. Be warned! ‚úåÔ∏è

reviews.name: Garland copeland
reviews.text: The sign said voted most popular for so many years so I gave it a try.  I really don't see how honestly. The food was really good but needs a bigger area for the buffet so they can expand the menu options. Specifically in the seafood options. Not having sushi was a let down. But the food on hand was delicious. This place could be absolutely fantastic if it had a revamp and expand the menu options and a larger buffet area. But as I said, the food on hand was delicious and cooked to perfection.

reviews.name: Frances Melissa

reviews.name: Robert Roan

reviews.name: Faith Baker

reviews.name: Bernetta Clements

reviews.name: Athena Sheffield
reviews.text: China Star hasn't been good the last few times I've been there. We went last night (07.23.2022) around 6:30 pm and there weren't very many customers, which is odd for a Friday night in Abilene. You could see that there were signs of wear and tear on the chairs and I would like to know what happened to their phone booth that they had for years and years. The food was definitely kept hot on the buffet, but the items just seemed to all taste the same as the item next to it...no uniqueness to it.

reviews.name: Rosemary . Zapata
reviews.text: We always eat here when we drive to Abilene.  This place has certainly gone downhill. The ladies restroom was dirty and the toilet paper on the floor and it smelled. My husband said the men's restroom smelled, was dirty with black mildew.

reviews.name: Elizabeth Lambert

If you live in Abilene and haven't gone here.... WHAAAAAT. ARE. YOU. DOING. And if you have, and don't like it, leave my city immediately. That's all

reviews.name: John North
reviews.text:
It's a buffet that was better before the pandemic.
Beef and broccoli was inedible as the beef was way overcooked.  The crab and broccoli salad had way too much mayonnaise and little crab.
Their wontons, shrimp, and chicken were still decent.
Fair value as you get all you care to eat.

reviews.name: Ron M
reviews.text: Came for the lunch buffet after a couple year absence. I think it will be a longer absence this time. It was 12:45 when I went in. I would not have thought so much of the food could be that dried out before the lunch hour was over but it was. If it wasn't in a sauce it was hard and dried. The spring rolls and egg rolls were tough and stuck to the pan. The dim sum were very tough and hard. As was the fried shrimp and the sweet and sour chicken. The won ton soup was either very watered down or they forgot to put salt in it. The fried rice was OK, as were the dishes with a sauce base although a couple of them were flavorless. The dessert selection was fine. Kudos for no longer allowing smoking in the restaurant. Last time I was there they still did. The service was excellent, very friendly and frequent. Overall not a very good dining experience. I will try next door.

reviews.name: Cathy Carroll
reviews.text: Some of the food had a funny taste.  The table, chair & buffet area was sticky. This is not as good as it used to be.  You would think with the money they make they could replace the carpet. This place needs to close for a good thorough cleaning and improvements.

reviews.name: T. B.
reviews.text: I cannot say enough good things about this restaurant. Everyone has always been polite, courteous and professional. Sometimes we get the buffet to go and eat in the leisure of our home. The to-go plates are the most reasonable in town. The food is always fresh and outstanding. Thanks to the entire staff....

reviews.name: Douglas Paulson
reviews.text: Met the owner, who was personally asking how the food was, making sure service was timely and up to standards. All staff were polite and food was great, will definitely visit again.

reviews.name: Jeannie Ferington
reviews.text: China Star offers a variety of food dishes. The dining room is usually very clean as is the buffet area. We have visited this establishment at least 3 times. Their tea often tastes unusual and requires us to switch drinks. Some of the food items on the buffet are cold when they should be hot. Have also became ill after eating here on 2 different occasions.

reviews.name: Dana Baldwin
reviews.text: Needs some serious attention.  I'll start off by saying the staff was fantastic, but that was the only plus.  The food had been on the buffet far too long and that meant that most things were overcooked, dried out and some was inedible.  The restaurant could use with a deep carpet cleaning and buffet equipment deep cleaning, too.

reviews.name: Cyn C

reviews.name: Lori Davis

reviews.name: Douglas Holt

The whole place smelled slightly moldy. It was a bit of a shame because at one time the decor must have been very nice with real wood paneling and fancy millwork decorations. A bit of TLC could move the place from meh to Yeah based on the food if it was cleaned up a bit.

reviews.name: LISSA ‚ÄúLissa‚Äù M

Today the food was just horrible, soogy smelled strange, some was way over cooked and the was just plain undercooked.

reviews.name: Ryan Berry

reviews.name: C.L. Becker

reviews.name: Fifi Boland

reviews.name: Malana Morrison
reviews.text: This restaurant is not very nice. The room with the buffet was humid/moldy and smelled bad. They had a Honeywell fan trying to dry things out. The heat lamps above the food we're disgusting with black spots all over them. The food was cold and not tasty. The ice cream machine was broken. I would definitely not recommend this place and actually wonder how the health department allows it to continue to operate.

reviews.name: Dave Lynch
reviews.text:
I am here out of town for only a few days. I read the reviews on this restaurant and they seemed good. I walked in and with a minute and a half I had my food on a plate. They are very quick and efficient. The food was good the people put it over the top. Very friendly staff. I went to check out and the man noticed my camouflage  wallet. He asked if I was in the military and I
am. He offered me 10 percent off without my  even having to ask him. I would recommend this restaurant to anyone who wanted good Chinese food

reviews.name: Charles
reviews.text:
We had the buffet, which was $13.00 plus tax for each of us. Some of the heated buffet food that should have been hot was cool, some luke-warm and some food was hot. The flavors were okay and not so exciting or in my expectations of Asian foods and for wanting Chinese food for a change.
I have had far better Chinese food in San Franciso, California, and Dallas, Texas, for that matter. The next time I want Chinese food, I will try the other resturants in Abilene, Texas, and see how they are in taste and quality.
The waitress was a little bossy, smart off about the buffet food, and that stuck in my mind and not so kind.

reviews.name: ANGEL PACANINS
reviews.text: Idk why I go back to this place. Lunch is 2 to 3 dollars higher than any other lunch buffet. The service is absolutely horrible from the managers, waiters take care of you good they are really only shining star at this place.  I got there at 11 30 am and the food was cold .  Lastly when I see some one in their parking lot who is hungry and I offer to pay for them to get a (semi) hot meal the manager or receptionist gives them the third degree.  I even had them get it to go so they would have to be judged as they ate.  In Abilene there are 2 or 3 better choices for this type of meal at a better price for better service.  If you choose to eat here expect to be treated like they are doing you a favor by what appears to be the ppl running the place.

We called to see to bring it to the attention to the manager that the food wasn't as good as it has been previously.  The manager responded by saying," what do you want me to do about it?." Managers that don't care about concerns from their customers don't deserve my money. I was just disappointed because I had such a great meal previously.

reviews.name: Fifi Boland

Will definitely visit again soon.

reviews.name: Darla Fullerton

reviews.name: Russell Henderson
reviews.text:
I recently visited Little Panda in Abilene and was disappointed by my experience. The atmosphere was outdated and lacked any real character, feeling more like a generic Chinese restaurant rather than a unique dining experience. The food was average at best, with dishes lacking any real depth of flavor and tasting quite bland. The menu was limited and lacked any real creativity, with most of the dishes feeling uninspired.

The service was also lacking, with staff who seemed disinterested in their job and provided slow, inattentive service. They were unhelpful when it came to menu recommendations and seemed more focused on their own tasks than making sure the customers were satisfied.

The combination of lackluster atmosphere, average food, and poor service made for a forgettable dining experience. If you're looking for truly delicious Chinese cuisine in Abilene, there are better options out there.

reviews.name: Larry Killian
reviews.text: I'd like to say something about this place that I think everbody in the whole Big Country should know. Harvest Moon is the best Chinese place on the planet. I started eating there as an ACU student in 1991. I've been to other places in town and there's absolutely no comparison. Amy is the friendliest most professional server anybody could hope for. She loves her job and she truly cares for her customers. She always gives 200% and when she's having a bad day you can't ever tell because she's always smiling and continuously courteous to everybody she meets. I have been in this town for the better part of the last 25 years and when I was in Waco for 6 years I always regretted leaving Abilene and Harvest Moon was at the top of the list.Waco has some great restaurants and the people are awesome but there wasn't a place in Mc Clennan county or even central Texas that compared to Harvest Moon. I've had at least 15 birthdays in this town and at least 7 of them were spent at Harvest Moon. Even when my friends offered to take me other places I always ask for HM. In fact we just call it the Moon and they know what I'm talking about. So in short, yea right, I'd highly recommended the Harvest Moon. Tell all your friends and as many people as will listen. About the only bad thing I can say is that they're closed on Saturday nights. I don't understand that but I'm sure there's a reasonable explanation. So go spend your $ at Harvest Moon. Ask for Amy if you can get her because she's the best but be prepared because she's very popular. I have great things to say about Juan and La Mom too but I hope they won't hold it against me for singing the praises of Amy. Great food, excellent service, and extremely reasonable prices. I know you all work hard for your $ and so do I but trust me it's more than well worth it. So that's it Abilene is a great town with very friendly and hard working God fearing people and Harvest Moon is the best Chinese food on the planet. Thank you may God bless each and every one of you who reads this and/or tells their friends and I wish you all a very pleasant day. God bless Abilene, Texas and the greatest country in the world the United States of America.  PS We all get to share this wonderful world we live in people, let's all try to get along and make the most of the time we have left. Life is short but also very precious. Have a great day.
